parameters:
\OC[30]\N<Philis>The adventurer's guild is located \C[17] southeast
from here. I will also listen to the stories from
those who visit the church.

\OC[30]\N<Philis>So far it seems like we at the monastery haven't
been affected by 'Nightmare Heaven' much. This is
also thanks to the blessings of the Holy Demon.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>How is that adventurer we encountered in the
dungeon doing?

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>They have calmed down quite a bit. Although they
are still staying in a private room, there
shouldn't be any issues with having everyday
conversations.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>However, it seems like they don't remember much
about what happened in the dungeon, so it's
unlikely that we'll be able to gather much
information...

\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see. However, we have found someone who can
investigate about 'Nightmare Heaven', so there
shouldn't be any issues.
\OC[31]\N<Rain>So, let's have him focus on healing his body.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>Yes, that's right. I can't dispel the curse right
now, but I will diligently find a way to deal with
it and show you.
\OC[31]\N<Rain>Well then, I'll take my leave now.

\OC[30]\N<Philis>Yes, take care. May the blessings of the Holy
Demon be with you.
\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Philis...? Are you spacing out? Are you okay...?

\CE[94]\CE[96]\OC[30]\N<Philis>Ah, s-sorry...! I-I'm fine...! I was just lost in
thought...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... If it's okay with me, please feel free to
consult with me if anything happens.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Philis, I came to check on you. How is that
adventurer doing?

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>Yes, umm... well, I think they're doing fine and
starting to calm down a bit.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>────Seems kind of vague ... Was there any problem
or something?

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>N-No... umm... nothing of the sort ...────. It's
just that, I'm getting worn out from 'treatment',
so I might be a little tired...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... Philis is the only one capable of
protecting against 'Nightmare Heaven' at the
monastery... It must be putting a lot of strain on
you.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Please wait a little longer as I try to find the
magic device as soon as possible...! Well then,
excuse me!

\OC[30]\N<Philis>(────I, I can't say it... that we're doing...
naughty things and helping each other reach
climax...)

\OC[30]\N<Philis>(But, he said that doing that has helped him calm
down quite a bit...Since we've come this far, I
can't just stop now...)

\OC[30]\N<Philis>(If I can ward off the power of Nightmare Heaven
using protection and assistance... then, I have to
do my best...I can't just rely on Rain
completely...)
\CE[79]\CE[84]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... Even with the power of your blessing...

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>Yes... It seems difficult to completely prevent
'Nightmare Heaven'...

\OC[30]\N<Philis>That magic seems to constantly circulate through
space like a gas, so even if we temporarily negate
its effects, it will still amplify desires again
over time...

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>By the way... I think places and people protected
by the divine blessings are relatively safe, but
how do we deal with those who are not protected?

\CE[79]\CE[78]\CE[83]\OC[31]\N<Rain>────Those whose desires have been amplified often
seek money... or they frequently come seeking
physical intimacy... it happens a lot...

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>It seems that most people easily amplify their
sexual desires...  So, for those individuals... we
try to respond to their desires as much as
possible...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>────It is better than causing harm to ordinary
people, and...

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>And... I've also been affected by the effects of
'Nightmare Heaven' to some extent... S-So, in
other words, there are times when it gets resolved
for me too...

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I-I'm sorry for surprising you... B-But, this is
the only solution we can currently come up with...

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>Y-Yes, that's right...!  No, sacrificing myself to
protect the people of the town from the clutches
of evil...!

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>────Please keep this a secret from Caldo and
Frist...

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>Yes... But... please take good care of your
body... If you need any treatment, please let me
know anytime...
\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Hey, Philis... Your face is all red, isn't it?

\CE[94]\CE[96]\OC[30]\N<Philis>Eh... Is that so? Well, there's nothing wrong with
me...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Is that so... considering the situation, please
don't push yourself too hard and remember to rest.

\N<Philis>Rain... um, I'm having trouble with where to
look... so if you could wear clothing with a
little less exposure, I would appreciate it...
EMW_メッセージウィンドウ指定 1

Huh... why is there someone dressed so
provocatively here... m-maybe they're just
tired...

Lately, my concentration has been easily
disrupted... Focus, focus...!
EMW_メッセージウィンドウ強制終了 1

\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I put them in a private room...for now, but is it
really okay to protect them here?

\OC[31]\N<Rain>Even though it's because of magic, he is still a
danger like this. Wouldn't it be better if we put
him in a prison cell at the guard station...?

\CE[94]\CE[79]\OC[30]\N<Philis>I see... but that person is the victim, so it
would be pitiful to put them in a prison cell...

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>Besides, there are other monks here, so I'm sure
it'll be fine!

\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>───... I understand. However, please let me know
immediately if you need any help.
\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>Rain, what are you going to do from now on?

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>For now, I understand that 'Nightmare Heaven'
cannot be dispelled by the usual method.

\CE[78]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>If even the experts in healing and dispelling
curses from the church can't undo it, honestly,
right now we have no choice but to accept it...

\CE[78]\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>But, Philis' treatment has slightly alleviated his
symptoms. And the fact that he can resist with
magic and mental strength like me means that there
must be a solution.
Rain: There must be a way.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>In order to find that, I will try to find someone
who can use the fragments of the device I picked
in the dungeon as a clue to analyze this magic.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>I see...! If we can analyze it, we might be able
to find a way to dispel the curse!

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Do you know of any places in this town where
magicians might gather?

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>In that case, there is an Adventurer's Guild in
this town located southeast from here, there might
be some magicians there.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>I'm sorry for being a burden... I don't seem to be
of much help right now...

\CE[79]\CE[84]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>No, I haven't been able to do anything yet either.
Philis, I'm counting on you to take care of him on
the second floor.

\CE[94]\OC[30]\N<Philis>All right. May the blessings of the Holy Demon be
with us.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\CE[84]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(That eerie aura... It was present when he
attacked me in the dungeon too... That's probably
the very desire that overflowed from Nightmare
Heaven...!)

\CE[78]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(If things continue like this... according to
Demon's words, does that mean all the residents of
this town will end up in a state like him...?)

\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(Until we find a solution, we have to somehow
satisfy \C[17]desires and help them regain some
rationality\C[13]...!)
Events in town have been unlocked.
'Lets go to the Adventurers Guild and look for a magician'

\N<\N[5]>"I see, the clear crystal was stolen by the
thief..."

\N<\N[5]>"But, thank goodness Sister Philis and Rain
have both returned safely. Let's first rejoice in
that."

\N<\N[5]>"However, Sister Philis, you've been too reckless.
Despite the situation, going off alone like
that..."

\N<Frist>However, I'm glad that Sister Philis and Rain have
both returned safely. First, let's rejoice in that
fact.

\N<Frist>However, Sister Philis, you're being too reckless.
Even considering the circumstances, going alone
like that...
\N<Philis>I'm sorry... but if we continue like this...

\N<Rain>Let's ask the guards to search for the clear
crystal. It may not be found immediately, but I
think it's better than doing nothing...

\N<Frist>I see... However, we still need to hurry and find
a fundamental solution...

\N<Rain>Yes... Since the thief was always one step ahead
of me and Philis, there's a high possibility that
we're being watched. If we act recklessly, we'll
just end up getting in the way again...

\N<Rain>I think I know the location of the third device
soon, so I'll go there. But please be careful here
and at the church as well.

\N<Philis>I was able to make one with the clear crystal we
retrieved. I think it's better if Rain has it.

\N<Philis>It should be able to prevent some 'Desire
Manipulation Techniques', and although it's only
once, if you break it, a temporarily powerful
protective force will be activated!
\N<Rain>Thank you very much. This will be our trump card.

\N<Philis>I hate to say this... but Rain, please be careful
not to push yourself too hard!
